items.title: 9 dead in fire at assisted-living facility: Officials
items.description: Nine people have been killed and dozens are hurt as a fire tore through an assisted-living facility in Fall River, Massachusetts, officials said.

items.title: WATCH:  Paraglider hits phone lines and plunges into river
items.description: Rescue teams retrieved the man and there were no reports of injuries.

items.title: WATCH:  Huge military parade in Paris to mark Bastille Day
items.description: French troops, as well as a range of military hardware, paraded down and flew over the Champs-Élysées to mark Bastille Day.

items.title: Texas flooding live updates: Search continues for missing with 130 dead
items.description: More than 130 people are dead after devastating flooding in the Texas Hill Country that began early on the Fourth of July.

items.title: A military exercise drawing together 19 nations and 35,000 forces begins in Australia
items.description: Australia is hosting its largest-ever military drills, Exercise Talisman Sabre, involving over 35,000 personnel from 19 nations
